---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ProfileCard from "../components/ProfileCard.astro";
---

<Layout
  currentPage="intro"
  title="Jeff Goseland | ML Engineer"
  description="Principal ML Engineer with production experience at Walmart and Acorns, exploring music cognition and human-centered AI systems."
>
  <div class="page page-wide intro-layout">
    <ProfileCard />
    <div class="intro-content">
      <p class="lead">
        Twenty years at Walmart designing multi-echelon MILP systems across 23 fulfillment
        centers, with documented supply chain impact measured in hundreds of millions of
        dollars. Currently building production ML at Acorns: winback modeling on Databricks
        with MLflow and SHAP.
      </p>
      <p class="lead">
        MS in Data Science, University of Notre Dame (May 2026). Also building
        <a href="https://noeticiq.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NoeticIQ</a>,
        a consulting brand at the intersection of data and cognition.
        See <a href="/education">Education</a> for academic background.
      </p>

      <h2 class="intro-heading">Research Interests</h2>
      <ul class="content-list">
        <li>Music cognition: emotional trajectory, arousal/valence, Tonnetz geometry</li>
        <li>Optimization: MILP, integer programming, constraint design</li>
        <li>Human-centered AI systems with interpretable interfaces</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Exploring PhD paths in music cognition plus optimization: ML/CS with a music focus,
        or music informatics with an optimization angle. Preference for local/part-time,
        remote funded international, or selective full-time programs.
      </p>

      <p class="philosophy">
        <em>All models are approximations. Usefulness beats precision. Interpretability matters in human-centered domains.</em>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
